&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>If x and y are continuous functions of t on an interval I, then the equations are called parametric equations and t is called the parameter
$$x=x(t) andy=y(t)$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Eliminating the Parameter 化简
&lt;div id="eliminating-the-parameter-%E5%8C%96%E7%AE%80" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
